Incident Response > [T3]: Lab - Suricata: Analyze a PCAP

Analyze a PCAP and match it against Suricata signatures

In this demo, we will be using Suricata against 2017-06-28-traffic-analysis-exercise.pcap, and in doing so, head to: 

cd $HOME/Desktop/CCD/Suricata/pcap 

Then execute the command:

sudo suricata -r 2017-06-28-traffic-analysis-exercise.pcap 

Successful execution will result in the creation of four new files in the current directory.

Checking the first ten lines from fast.log by executing the following: 

cat fast.log  | head -n10 

You will notice the stages of downloading the malware and the C&C communications.
